overview: The user initiated a request for a complete aesthetic overhaul of
  their sleep questionnaire application, expressing dissatisfaction with its
  current generic appearance. The assistant began by conducting a thorough
  review of the app's existing visual design, examining global styles, layout,
  and individual UI components. Based on this analysis, a new design strategy
  was formulated, focusing on a calming, sleep-themed aesthetic. The
  implementation involved updating the color palette to incorporate deeper
  indigo/purple tones with soft teal accents, refining typography, and enhancing
  the overall layout of the QuestionnaireForm. Key UI components like the
  progress bar, checkboxes, sliders, and radio groups were restyled for a more
  polished look. Additionally, the IntroSection was redesigned for a better
  welcome experience, and the DaytimeSection's grouping styles were improved to
  serve as a template for other sections, transforming the app's visual language
  to be more nuanced and trustworthy.
